OL,4,CMillions more middle-aged are obese,
OL,5,Cstudy suggests
OL,6,GMillions of middle-aged people have
OL,7,Gbeen mistakenly led to believe they
OL,8,Gare not obese, according to an Italian
OL,9,Gstudy that looked at body fat instead
OL,10,Gof weight related to height.
OL,12,FUsing a new, lower cut-off for obesity
OL,13,Fwould give a truer picture of who is
OL,14,Faffected, the researchers say.
OL,16,FWith age, muscle declines and fat
OL,17,Fbuilds up around organs in the waist
OL,18,Fregion, often with no change in weight.
OL,20,FThe challenge is to find a tool that
OL,21,Feasily screens for obesity.
